summary: Compiled historical delivery data, analyst estimates, and market forecasts for Tesla Q1 2026
content:
# Tesla Q1 2026 Delivery Research

## Historical Q1 Deliveries
- Q1 2024: 386,810 vehicles (normal quarter)
- Q1 2025: 336,681 vehicles (depressed by Model Y changeover)

## Recent Quarters
- Q3 2025: 497,099 (record, tax credit pull-forward)
- Q4 2025: 418,227 (down 16% YoY)

## Full Year Trends
- 2024: 1,789,226 vehicles
- 2025: 1,636,129 vehicles (down 8.6%)
- Second consecutive year of decline

## Analyst Estimates Q1 2026
- Barclays (Dan Levy): ~350,000 units
- Morgan Stanley: -9.3% YoY (~305,000)

## Kalshi Market Prices
- 83% chance of 300,000+
- 57% chance of 330,000+
- 36% chance of 340,000+
- 21% chance of 360,000+
- 9% chance of 380,000+
â†’ Implied median: ~330,000

## Regional Challenges
- Europe 2025: Down 27.8% (Germany -48.4%)
- China 2025: Down 7% (851,732 Shanghai shipments)
- US: No $7,500 tax credit (expired Sept 2025)
- BYD overtook Tesla as #1 EV seller (2.26M in 2025)
